Explanation
- In PrintShopController.java the handler method getPrintShopSatisfiedRequests is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/satisfied", method = RequestMethod.GET)
  There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly /printshops/satisfied.
- The mapping explicitly specifies RequestMethod.GET, so only GET is declared acceptable.
- There is no @RequestMapping for this path without a method (which would accept all methods) and no explicit mappings for HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE or PATCH for this same path in the provided source. Therefore those methods are not marked as acceptable by the code.
- Note: I did not assume any implicit framework behavior (such as automatic HEAD support for GET handlers); acceptance is determined only from explicit code annotations as requested.
